text-output: baby another stork delivers a bundle on a doorstep it's two kittens nearby a third stork leaves two puppies by a doghouse it takes flight again joining the rest of the flock the birds flap their wide graceful wings as they disappear into the clouds

later they emerge high above the ground each stork approaches its own fluffy cloud as one lands its cloud smiles and presents a new bundle the others continue to land on their own pink clouds one cloud molds a kitten and zaps it with lightning bringing it to life
it grooms itself another cloud creates a puppy the cloud makes a bone and the doggy shakes it in its jaws a cloud makes a baby human the cloud makes a football it puts a helmet on the baby

the cloud takes away the helmet and wraps up the child in a bundle below the laughing clouds floats another lonely looking cloud he rolls a piece of himself like dough adds four legs and zaps it with lightning creating a baby alligator it snaps its jaws the cloud picks it up and wags a scolding finger which the

alligator bites off the finger grows back an out of breath stork flies over and lands on the cloud the stork salutes the cloud gives it a noogie the stork playfully pets its face with its beak then motions for him to hand over the baby the
cloud holds out the alligator it chomps on the stork's head the cloud yanks the alligator off and wraps it in a bundle with its beak the stork holds it out far in front of its body and flies off

later the cloud fashions another baby the out of breath stork flies up as it salutes a bunch of feathers drop from its scrawny wing the cloud brings his sculpture to life a baby ram butts the stork with its horns knocking the wind out of the bird the cloud picks up the young goat

the stork looks up at a puppy running around another cloud the doggy gets some of the cloud stuck on its face and sneezes it happily licks its stork the lonely cloud frowns at his bundled baby ram his stork notices and sheepishly stops laughing the

cloud places the bundle into its beak and it butts the bird repeatedly as it flies off later the stork returns the cloud turns to face it with a new sculpted baby the stork cowers then grabs it with its wings just as the cloud brings it to life it's a prickly porcupine the stork flings it from wing to

wing playing hot potato with it with each toss the bird gets more and more quills stuck in its feathers the cloud takes the porcupine and bundles it up the baby's needle sharp quills poke out of the cloth the bird carefully takes it and flies off now the stork returns with a bunch of quills poking out of its head like an afro the cloud yanks them out accidentally

plucking feathers along with them he hugs the stork then shows a cloudy baby shark the stork flutters backward the bird sees a cute flock of chicks bouncing around another cloud the lonely cloud holds out the molded baby shark his stork flies off to another cloud glowing pink with sunlight
the lonely cloud crushes the unfinished baby shark as he folds his arms and mopes lightning strikes downward from his base he sees the pink cloud giving his stork a bundle the
lonely cloud turns away from them he starts to rain a feather floats past his bulbous nose he turns to find his stork flying down to him the bird opens up its bundle

the stork takes out a set of football pads and a helmet and puts them on the bird demonstrates how hard its helmet is the cloud gives the stork a big bear hug the bird motions for him to hand over a baby the cloud brings a snakelike eel to life and it electrocutes the stork
